---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';

const bullets = [
  'Produced social media graphics and campaign visuals aligned with Frostic\'s playful brand system.',
  'Designed promotional materials for different activations including token launches, event attendance, and leaderboard announcements.',
  'Created visuals for Telegram-native gamified experiences and community challenges.',
  'Contributed to the visual identity consistency across all public-facing channels.',
  'Developed a library of reusable assets that the team could adapt independently.',
];
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Frostic"
  description="Graphic design for Frostic, an AI digital twin platform for character IP. Social media visuals and gamified Telegram experiences."
  tags={['content', 'design', 'comms']}
  meta={[
    { label: 'Role',   value: 'Graphic Designer' },
    { label: 'Client', value: 'Frostic'          },
    { label: 'Year',   value: '2025'             },
  ]}
  heroImage="/img-frostic-01.jpg"
  images={[
    '/img-frostic-02.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-03.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-04.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-05.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-06.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-07.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-08.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-09.jpg',
    '/img-frostic-10.jpg',
  ]}
  linkLabel="view twitter profile"
  linkHref="https://x.com/frosticxyz"
>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The context</h2>
    <p>Frostic is an AI digital twin platform built around character IP — a world of collectible characters with on-chain identities, gamified social experiences, and a native utility token ($FROST). The project lives at the intersection of AI, gaming, and crypto, with a community built primarily around Telegram and X. I worked with their team to produce the visual content that brought the brand to life across every channel they operated.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The problem</h2>
    <p>Frostic had a strong concept and a distinctive visual world, but producing content consistently at the pace the community expected was a challenge. Announcements, game updates, token launches, leaderboard reveals — everything needed to look polished and on-brand, fast. The team needed a design partner who could absorb the brand language quickly and deliver at speed without losing quality or coherence.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">What I did</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      {bullets.map(item => (
        <li class="bullet-list__item">
          <img src="/icon-bullet-list.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="bullet-list__icon" width="8" height="8" />
          <span>{item}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The result</h2>
    <p>A consistent visual presence across Frostic's most active growth period — covering token launches, EthCC activation, community leaderboards, and the rollout of live character features. The design system I built into reusable templates let the team keep the momentum going independently after our engagement, without losing the visual quality the community had come to expect.</p>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>
